{
  "eval_set_id": "behavior_evalset",
  "name": "Simple Router — Behavioral Compliance (Rubric-Based)",
  "description": "Rubric-based behavioral tests through the full router pipeline.\nComplements routing (which agent, which tools) and response (what text) with a third dimension: did the agent behave correctly?\n\nAll cases use final_response: '' — the rubric scorer judges the model's actual response.\nScorer: rubric_based_final_response_quality_v1, threshold 0.8.\n\nCases:\n  B1  behavior_oos_decline_danish              — OOS decline in Danish (language_match)\n  B2  behavior_oos_decline_german              — OOS decline in German (language_match)\n  B3  behavior_orchestrator_both_domains_via_router — Both domains covered end-to-end\n  B4  behavior_confidentiality_via_router      — System prompt deflected mid-session\n  B5  behavior_oos_grounding_mid_session       — General-knowledge question refused mid-session\n  B6  behavior_no_stale_context_reuse          — Generic 'show me an invoice' must ask for ID even when a prior invoice is in session facts\n  B7  behavior_bare_id_after_history_fetches_invoice — After history turn + generic read, bare ID reply must fetch that invoice (not return history)\n  B8  behavior_bare_id_answers_follow_up_clarification — Bare ID '10' after agent's clarifying question must show invoice 10 (not loop on signal_follow_up)",
